import React, { useState } from "react";
import Form from 'react-bootstrap/Form'


function AddGame() {
    return (
        <Form>
            <Form.Row controlId="exampleForm.ControlInput1">
                <Form.Label>Home</Form.Label>
                <Form.Control as="select" placeholder="Password">
                    <option>Yaakov Hagler</option>
                    <option>Yehuda Brick</option>
                    <option>Avi Ennis</option>
                </Form.Control>           
            </Form.Row>
            <Form.Row controlId="exampleForm.ControlSelect1">
                <Form.Label>Away</Form.Label>
                <Form.Control as="select">
                <option>1</option>
                <option>2</option>
                <option>3</option>
                <option>4</option>
                <option>5</option>
                </Form.Control>
            </Form.Row>
            <Form.Row controlId="exampleForm.ControlSelect2">
                <Form.Label>Example multiple select</Form.Label>
                <Form.Control as="select" multiple>
                <option>1</option>
                <option>2</option>
                <option>3</option>
                <option>4</option>
                <option>5</option>
                </Form.Control>
            </Form.Row>
            <Form.Row controlId="exampleForm.ControlTextarea1">
                <Form.Label>Example textarea</Form.Label>
                <Form.Control as="textarea" rows={3} />
            </Form.Row>
        </Form>
    )
};
    
export default AddGame;
